 {"id":"bd-1dfc","title":"P6.14h: Connector fixtures from real sessions (no mock dirs)","description":"# P6.14h: Connector fixtures from real sessions (no mock dirs)

## Goal
Eliminate synthetic "mock-*" directory naming and ensure connector tests use real session fixtures with provenance metadata.

## Why
Many connector tests use temp dirs named `mock-claude` etc. Even if fixtures are real, the naming and setup still imply mocked data. We want a clear, real-fixture pipeline and provenance hashing.

## Plan
1. Rename fixture setup to use `fixtures/<agent>/...` (real session samples).
2. Add a provenance manifest for fixtures (source, capture date, redaction policy, hash).
3. Update connector tests to reference real fixture paths and verify provenance hash in logs.
4. Ensure temp dirs are still used for isolation but seeded from real fixtures.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Connector tests no longer create "mock-*" directory names.
- Fixture provenance is documented and hashed.
- Tests pass without relying on mocked file structures.

